“I WENT AND I DID IT!”

I vividly remember my first phone call with my dad in 2010.  I had just moved to Atlanta for college & it had been a few years since we had any communication. 

I was telling him about what I was majoring in college and why I wanted to be in Atlanta (for hair) and my plans for making the dream life I had envisioned come true. Long story short as the conversation turned argument was ending he said "yea ok good luck on that pole or in them streets” before hanging the phone up on me. I was like well DAMN!!! That was by far the last thing I ever expected from anybody to tell me on my new journey in a new city at 18 years old, but especially from my dad. Anybody that REALLY knew me back then in middle/high school knew that I ALWAYS had an interest in hair. 

I think about that conversation more than I’d like to admit honestly.

People always ask me how do I keep going so hard for so long. Truth be told PAIN moves you in ways like no other! Also, to know me is to know I ALWAYS TURN MY LEMONS INTO LEMONADE!!!!

I always so thankful for my amazing clients like @bigdavescheesesteaks / @officialdhayes who TRULY believe in me and appreciate my talents! 

Dear Dad, you hurt me but it’s ok. Im ok. Look at me now! I never made it on any poles and the only “streets I’m in” is the streets of living my dreams and taking good care of myself. 🤷🏽‍♀️💯🙏🏽

Super heavy on “the price is the price”. I’m all about you get what you pay for! 

I’m one of those rare stylists that INCLUDES a shampoo, treatment, trim, blow dry, braid down, oil scalp, net, AND style with the price of my weaves! I mean why would I charge extra to do my part? 

As a stylist that is licensed with yearssss of experience it’s the ONLY way to do things in my opinion. I love making sure I take away as much stress from my clients as possible. 

This method has worked for me since the beginning of time! I was shampooing hair in my dorm room. ASK ABOUT ME! Never wanted to simply just take large amounts of money from individuals and only giving them the bare minimum. I’ve seen it so much in recent years it truly makes me angry lol. But hey.. to each it’s own 🙃. 

I have openings in Atlanta this week. Bundles available for sale as well. I’m also available for travel. Book the flight and I am on the way! 

Oh if you can’t tell… I LOVE TO CURL HAIR! 💁🏽‍♀️

We set the trends! 

Major shoutout to one of the elites @mrzothegoat !

I remember about 2 years ago I was doing Zo hair and he reminded me of something that happened like 10 yrs ago. He jokingly brought up a time where him his brother & our other friend came to Atlanta from SC one night & randomly needed somewhere to sleep that night. They called me up & I welcomed them over for a few hours to get rest to get back on road to SC. 

I was like aww man I forgot all about that lol that was just off the strength you know. I had a plenty of blankets and floor space to extend in my little college apartment 🤣🤷🏽‍♀️! We laughed it off because Zo is a millionaire now haha 😂 💯🔥! I’m like man I’d never tell anybody that these days. Just because I didn’t want to give off any “remember that time I helped you” vibes and have people thinking something negative. But he quickly said… “Actually you should tell people that story. Those that know you will understand and those that don’t, well the right ones who are meant to be around will not take that as a brag or such. I’d never forget that time you came through for us!” I was so shocked he even remembered that but he was right overall! I’m not in control of anybody’s else thought process 💯. 

Today when I was finishing up with his hair I just smiled to myself and said thank you lord! It always pays to be a good hearted human being. You never know how such a small gesture to you is something big to somebody else. If you’re in a position to help sometimes just do it. Do it without looking for anything in return or using it to throw back at somebody. 

Anywho, y’all see how I got my guy crispy for his upcoming photo shoot thought right? Link in bio to book. I’m available in Atlanta and for travel. Book the flight and I’ll be to the airport baby.

You ever feel like … DAMN I NEED A REAL MF BREAK FROM EVERYTHING & EVERYBODY?!!! 

Well… I honestly feel like that pretty often lol 🤷🏽‍♀️ but there was a point some months ago were I was like IM GETTING AWAY FROM EVERYONE AND EVERYTHING ASAP AND IDK FOR HOW LONG‼️ 

Life be “lifing” sometimes a bit to much lol. I packed some items up and bought a one way first class to Mexico. I had no idea when I would come back and was in no rush to figure it out either. 

I enjoyed 14 days of solo time and it was truly a blessing. I got to sleep with no alarm clock and eat absolutely anything I wanted too whenever I felt like it. I totally enjoyed my solo vacation and I highly recommend for others to indulge as well. 

I get asked a lot .. “you don’t be scared to travel alone?”… heavy on the NO. America is more dangerous if you ask me lol you’re more likely to get kidnapped, beat up, raped, and robbed right here 🙃. Stay vigilant but also remember you get one life so … live it… and NOT in FEAR! 

There was no way I could get 14 days into a 60 second clip but enjoy this quick preview of my time. 
 
I stayed in Playa Del Carmen. I traveled to Cancun and Tulum for fun going to excursions and parties etc while there.

My Airbnb was amazing and perfectly located in a central area walking distance to everything. 

I ate out and I grocery shopped. I didn’t rent a car to save money. Plus I wanted to be a “local” much as I could so I walked or caught the bus/taxi when needed. 

If you want to take a solo trip but have questions contact me now on my travel page @travelbaeabril

Last week I had the pleasure to attend Young Middle School in Atlanta, GA and it was absolutely AMAZING!!!! 

I spoke to 5 classes of students, totaling over 100 kids ranging from 12-14 year olds, one 7th grade class and four 8th grade classes. 

The initial purpose for my invite was for “Career Day” however with me, anytime I get an opportunity to present my “career” I use it to present “myself”. Without me always knowing who I am and remaining true to myself I would not have the career nor life that I currently have. 

Every single class I spoke to I walked out with kids crying from relatable situations and full of enthusiasm as I told my story and my “why”. Along with my main message that YOUR CURRENT SITUATIONS DO NOT DETERMINE YOUR FINAL OUTCOME FOR YOUR LIFE!!! 

If you know me you know I’ve been going back to the schools to volunteer for the pass 10+ years. I had my biggest event planned that got canceled the day the world began to shut down March 2020. It’s been a long 2 years since I’ve been granted the opportunity to enter the schools again and I did not take it for granted one bit! Shoutout to @itsmoodylove for the information and invite to her school! 

If you work at or know anybody who works with any schools in the Atlanta or surrounding areas please reach out to me. I would love to pour into your students and help add to the shaping and growth and development of their minds and their futures. I have a lot of experience and looking for more. I have a gift and it’s a must I share it with as many as possible. 

Book me now while I’m “free” because soon enough I will be entering paid gigs for my speaking engagements. Mark my words. 🫶🏽💯🗣️🗣️🗣️

Los Angeles dump ✈️ 

Fun fact! I flew to Los Angeles 32 times between 4 years (January 2018 - December 2021) just to do hair!!!

Covid completely ruined my travels so I had to take a break from going to work so much. 😒

TURN YO CLIQUE UP DAWG!!! 

That’s exactly what I’ve been doing since 2010 when I stepped foot onto the illustrious @cau1988 !

I’ve had the pleasure of servicing THOUSANDS of people in my 13 years of being in Atlanta. I would not be THEE “celebrity hairstylist A’bril Elon” today WITHOUT CAU! 

The first picture here is me smiling in front of the FIRST SALON I ever got to work out of on campus directly behind my college dorm room back in 2012. It was the BIGGEST learning lesson in my entire “hair career” I ever experienced. I worked there under an apprenticeship of an older lady who never showed up to the salon to teach me anything and then one day left and NEVER came back. I was crushed! I had lost all my hours I worked on while trying to obtain my college degree and cosmetology license at the same time. All while I was paying a weekly booth room much higher than I could even afford to pay. I remember trying to borrow money from family just to pay my rent weekly because I had to build clientele. I was doing “ok” but as broke college kids the income in compared to the amount of work I was putting in was not adding up just yet!

Needless to say I left my first “major” salon experience HURT but I did not let it stop me from moving forward. 

Fast forward to 2023 … 9 years after I have graduated from college with my degree & license. I literally serviced 20 people in just 2.5 days this week of homecoming. With zero exaggeration there were OVER ONE HUNDRED people at the tailgate whom I have serviced before. 

I am sooo proud of ME! I LOVE TO DO HAIR! IT IS MY HEART! If I’ve ever been able to have you in my chair you know my love for what I do and how I do it. I am so thankful for my journey and where it all started. 

Look at me now. BIG BRIL! I went from barely  doing 20 heads a month to doing 30 heads a week! Let’s talk about it! God is good. 

MAJOR THANK YOU TO ALL OF THOSE WHO HAVE BOOKED ME FOR ANY SERVICE OVER THE YEARS. ITS ALL APPRECIATED! 💇🏽‍♀️

I had the pleasure of being invited to @empirebeautyschool Augusta to speak with two combined classes of students! 

Mentoring has been a passion of mine for years. I’ve always poured back into the classroom since I was a teenager in college. No matter the age, race, nationality, education level, history etc EVERYONE can learn something from the next person. 

It’s always my goal to have walked away with knowing I’ve inspired and motivated those who have listened to my knowledge! I’ll never claim to know it all but I know A-LOT and I love to share it all with others. 

As I spoke on my story and how I’ve gotten to the point of success I’m at and plan to keep going I could see a shift in room. By the time I walked out the entire class was lifted in goals for their future in the beauty industry and as entrepreneurs. I absolutely love that for them!!!

As I navigate through life I’ve found myself going from volunteering my services to being invited out for them. It’s been a pleasure and I always look forward for the next time! Contact me soon to book me for your classroom or event!

Thanks to my favorite cosmetology teacher of all time @stronghairco for thinking of me when the opportunity came about at your new school. Even so….Always and Forever a Paul Mitchell Atlanta Girllllll 💇🏽‍♀️🥰🤭🫶🏽🗣️🤩🙏🏽

POV: this is your sign to take awkward photos with you bestfriend …. The DIY edition ! 

Sooooo…. At the last minute I realized I had about 36 hours in my weekend to spare! Me and my fav girl haven’t gotten to spend much time together this year so once I realized I had time I immediately booked a flight to visit! 

I LOVEEEE to surprise people so I didn’t want to tell her the idea about taking awkward photos at JCPenny! In my mind we were going to do a walk in appointment! Ahhhhhhh let’s be real I completely forgot it’s HOLIDAY SEASON so after a failed attempt at JCPenny I refused to leave town without us still having our photoshoot. I said well we going to have to do it outside ourself so let’s go to your crib and get the ring light stand and find a park or something. 

As soon as we set it up outside this nice lady, Mrs. Joyce, was passing by with her puppy and asked if we needed help. Murphye hesitated on the response but I immediately said YES! Lmaooo. Because All I could think about was us trying to use the timer running back and forth to take these pics looking even more ridiculous than the poses! 🤣🙄😒

15 mins later the mission was accomplished and we saved ALL of our money 🥰🤭🫱🏽‍🫲🏾 !

This is almost 17 years of friendship. Yes we still intentionally dress alike when we are together. Yes we refuse to “grow up”. Yes we go together REALLLL BADDDD. 👯‍♀️😛💅🏽 

Some of yall knew us as Abreezy & Murph Weezy, some by ABrilly & Murph Durf, and others know us by Elon Innovations and HBM! 

Either way to have known us or to know us you’ll know WE ALWAYS BEEN THEE VIBE!!!
